<chapter>
<num>CHAPTER 4—</num>
<heading>TAXATION</heading>
<subchapter>
<num>SUBCHAPTER I—</num>
<heading>FEDERAL RESERVE BANKS</heading>
<section>
<num>§ 531.</num>
<heading> Exemption from taxation</heading>
<content>
<p class="indent0">Federal reserve banks, including the capital stock and surplus therein and the income derived therefrom shall be exempt from Federal, State, and local taxation, except taxes upon real estate.</p>
</content>
<sourceCredit>(<ref>Dec. 23, 1913, ch. 6, § 7(c)</ref>, <ref>38 Stat. 258</ref>; <ref>Mar. 3, 1919, ch. 101, § 1</ref>, <ref>40 Stat. 1314</ref>; <ref>Pub. L. 103–66, title III, § 3002(c)(2)</ref>, <date date="1993-08-10">Aug. 10, 1993</date>, <ref>107 Stat. 338</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
</subchapter>
<subchapter>
<num>SUBCHAPTER II—</num>
<heading>NATIONAL BANK CIRCULATION</heading>
<section>
<num>§ 541.</num>
<heading> Tax on circulating notes generally</heading>
<content>
<p class="indent0">In lieu of all existing taxes, every association shall pay to the Treasurer of the United States, in the months of January and July, a duty of one-half of 1 per centum each half year upon the average amount of its notes in circulation.</p>
</content>
<sourceCredit>(R.S. § 5214; <ref>Mar. 3, 1883, ch. 121, § 1</ref>, <ref>22 Stat. 488</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
