<subchapter>
<num>SUBCHAPTER III—</num>
<heading>NATIONAL BANK SHARES</heading>
<section>
<num>§ 548.</num>
<heading> State taxation</heading>
<content>
<p class="indent0">For the purposes of any tax law enacted under authority of the United States or any State, a national bank shall be treated as a bank organized and existing under the laws of the State or other jurisdiction within which its principal office is located.</p>
</content>
<sourceCredit>(R.S. § 5219; <ref>Mar. 4, 1923, ch. 267</ref>, <ref>42 Stat. 1499</ref>; <ref>Mar. 25, 1926, ch. 88</ref>, <ref>44 Stat. 223</ref>; <ref>Pub. L. 91–156</ref>, §§ 1(a), 2(a), <date date="1969-12-24">Dec. 24, 1969</date>, <ref>83 Stat. 434</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
